1
00:00:55,622 --> 00:00:59,872
When people finish their day
and hurry home,

2
00:01:00,539 --> 00:01:02,206
my day starts.

3
00:01:19,747 --> 00:01:23,914
My diner is open from midnight
to 7:00 in the morning.

4
00:01:24,461 --> 00:01:27,503
They call it "Midnight Diner."

5
00:01:33,279 --> 00:01:35,271
Do I even have customers?

6
00:01:35,271 --> 00:01:37,146
More than you would expect.

7
00:01:39,581 --> 00:01:41,622
MIDNIGHT DINER: TOKYO STORIES

8
00:01:41,622 --> 00:01:47,777
CHICKEN FRIED RICE

9
00:01:48,692 --> 00:01:51,990
ON PATROL

10
00:01:58,702 --> 00:02:01,160
This is still here, not sold?

11
00:02:02,185 --> 00:02:06,768
I don't care if he's sold or not.
I want him to stay now.

12
00:02:07,468 --> 00:02:08,718
You feel attached to him.

13
00:02:09,630 --> 00:02:11,713
Yes, I know it's only junk.

14
00:02:13,430 --> 00:02:14,596
Oh, it's about time.

15
00:02:14,866 --> 00:02:16,699
-Thank you.
-Okay.

16
00:02:23,089 --> 00:02:23,923
Here you are.

17
00:02:23,924 --> 00:02:25,279
Exact amount.

18
00:02:25,279 --> 00:02:26,812
What's that?

19
00:02:26,812 --> 00:02:27,645
This?

20
00:02:32,306 --> 00:02:34,598
It's like a merry-go-round.

21
00:02:35,315 --> 00:02:37,399
He is lonely on his own, though.

22
00:02:37,399 --> 00:02:39,063
This won't sell, either.

23
00:02:39,063 --> 00:02:41,783
It's just walking the same spot
again and again.

24
00:02:41,783 --> 00:02:44,241
Like our life.

25
00:02:44,628 --> 00:02:47,745
Be lost in thought later.
Let's get back to work.

26
00:02:47,745 --> 00:02:49,578
You're right. See you.

27
00:02:49,578 --> 00:02:50,798
Thank you.

28
00:02:53,575 --> 00:02:56,700
I confirm the stolen wallet is in the bag.

29
00:02:57,435 --> 00:03:00,518
Yes, I will take him to Headquarters.

30
00:03:01,907 --> 00:03:04,115
Sorry to have bothered you, everyone.

31
00:03:05,581 --> 00:03:08,247
Stealing? What did this man steal?

32
00:03:09,384 --> 00:03:12,969
He has repeatedly stolen bags
at midnight movie theaters.

33
00:03:12,969 --> 00:03:15,722
- A habitual offender.
- I see.

34
00:03:15,722 --> 00:03:18,419
Because the movie theater is dark.

35
00:03:18,419 --> 00:03:22,352
Sometimes I was so into the movie,
I forgot to steal, though.

36
00:03:22,352 --> 00:03:23,523
For instance, recently--

37
00:03:23,523 --> 00:03:25,836
I'll listen to your film reviews
at the office.

38
00:03:25,836 --> 00:03:26,669
Yes.

39
00:03:27,872 --> 00:03:32,581
Thank you. We may need to ask you
more questions later.

40
00:03:32,581 --> 00:03:33,706
Sure.

41
00:03:40,397 --> 00:03:42,772
So, can I order whatever I'd like here?

42
00:03:44,215 --> 00:03:45,715
If I have enough ingredients.

43
00:03:46,514 --> 00:03:47,722
I see.

44
00:03:48,688 --> 00:03:52,463
It sounds like customers are given
more choices,

45
00:03:52,463 --> 00:03:54,838
but decisions are actually
led by the diner.

46
00:03:55,154 --> 00:03:56,779
What an interesting strategy.

47
00:03:57,129 --> 00:03:58,254
What's the strategy?

48
00:03:58,563 --> 00:04:00,063
Don't know.

49
00:04:00,660 --> 00:04:02,359
Can you make chicken rice?

50
00:04:02,618 --> 00:04:03,618
Sure.

51
00:04:04,281 --> 00:04:05,045
I can.

52
00:04:05,302 --> 00:04:06,932
Also a beer, please.

53
00:04:06,932 --> 00:04:07,932
Okay.

54
00:04:30,903 --> 00:04:32,030
Here you go.

55
00:04:34,707 --> 00:04:35,872
Thank you.

56
00:04:40,946 --> 00:04:41,946
How's it?

57
00:04:45,268 --> 00:04:46,393
Delicious!

58
00:04:47,158 --> 00:04:49,962
My name is Akai.
<i>"akai" = "red" (adjective)</i>

59
00:04:49,962 --> 00:04:52,212
That's why you wear red?

60
00:04:52,747 --> 00:04:56,821
Funny. You even order red-colored food.

61
00:04:57,428 --> 00:05:01,303
The color red gives you power.
Some people wear red underwear, you know.

62
00:05:08,156 --> 00:05:10,781
Don't you like peas?

63
00:05:11,781 --> 00:05:12,948
I didn't when I was a kid.

64
00:05:13,572 --> 00:05:14,906
But now...

65
00:05:18,886 --> 00:05:22,882
These days, I can't find any restaurant
that serves this old-style chicken rice.

66
00:05:26,235 --> 00:05:27,652
Since then,

67
00:05:28,119 --> 00:05:30,322
it seems he liked my chicken rice,

68
00:05:30,545 --> 00:05:32,719
and he's been coming here sometimes.

69
00:05:37,888 --> 00:05:40,196
Mr. Momi, this...

70
00:05:41,441 --> 00:05:43,524
It's Shinichiro Akai indeed.

71
00:05:43,742 --> 00:05:45,206
Is he that famous?

72
00:05:45,421 --> 00:05:47,838
He's a super famous game creator.

73
00:05:48,500 --> 00:05:50,334
Just the video games, right?

74
00:05:53,198 --> 00:05:55,948
The game he created, Door to Door,

75
00:05:56,531 --> 00:06:00,489
commonly known as D to D series,

76
00:06:01,156 --> 00:06:06,156
is a very popular one
and is played worldwide.

77
00:06:07,462 --> 00:06:08,620
Who are you?

78
00:06:08,990 --> 00:06:12,573
Mr. Momi is my game master.

79
00:06:12,834 --> 00:06:15,876
Master means my teacher
not as in diner's owner!

80
00:06:16,709 --> 00:06:18,292
Here, another one.

81
00:06:18,515 --> 00:06:19,807
Thanks.

82
00:06:20,156 --> 00:06:22,281
Why did he leave his business card?

83
00:06:23,457 --> 00:06:26,207
He said he's been asked to go on TV.

84
00:06:26,903 --> 00:06:30,270
They will make a
documentary about him.

85
00:06:30,506 --> 00:06:34,580
He asked me if it could be shot here, too.

86
00:06:34,580 --> 00:06:38,348
What? That's amazing!
Make sure you accept that!

87
00:06:41,118 --> 00:06:45,104
Anyway, I think he'd better
stop wearing those red suits.

88
00:06:45,400 --> 00:06:47,233
Even his name is Akai.

89
00:06:48,846 --> 00:06:54,640
Master, I think a man who can
only make silly jokes like that

90
00:06:54,640 --> 00:06:56,849
needs a walkthrough of life.

91
00:06:58,672 --> 00:07:02,506
Life, it's not like a game.
You can't reset it.

92
00:07:04,076 --> 00:07:08,117
Mr. Momi, you're so deep.

93
00:07:10,702 --> 00:07:13,184
We'll frame the paper lantern and...

94
00:07:13,184 --> 00:07:17,991
That's how they started
shooting a documentary here.

95
00:07:18,793 --> 00:07:19,960
Master.

96
00:07:20,508 --> 00:07:22,050
Please get ready to cook.

97
00:07:22,689 --> 00:07:23,772
Thank you.

98
00:07:24,195 --> 00:07:24,942
Like this?

99
00:07:25,169 --> 00:07:26,109
Okay.

100
00:07:26,740 --> 00:07:28,865
Mr. Akai, let's start.

101
00:07:29,408 --> 00:07:30,408
Sure.

102
00:07:31,508 --> 00:07:33,438
Set...

103
00:07:33,438 --> 00:07:35,385
Three, two...

104
00:07:38,814 --> 00:07:40,187
Excuse me...

105
00:07:40,187 --> 00:07:43,940
I've finished with the adjustments
you asked me to do yesterday.

106
00:07:43,940 --> 00:07:46,135
Quick work! Can I see it now?

107
00:07:46,135 --> 00:07:47,135
Of course.

108
00:07:47,711 --> 00:07:50,348
I'm happy with the movement of fingers,
but not the neck.

109
00:07:50,348 --> 00:07:51,981
The neck is important.

110
00:07:51,981 --> 00:07:54,481
It won't be dynamic enough
if it doesn't move like this.

111
00:07:54,820 --> 00:07:57,320
It won't be dynamic enough
if it doesn't move like this.

112
00:07:57,320 --> 00:08:01,486
It was when he was in high school
when Akai encountered video games.

113
00:08:02,086 --> 00:08:04,347
He says it was a means to escape reality.

114
00:08:04,347 --> 00:08:07,095
My husband used to be a barkeep.

115
00:08:07,095 --> 00:08:09,307
But he passed away five years ago.

116
00:08:09,307 --> 00:08:12,414
I have no children,
and as long as I don't employ anyone,

117
00:08:12,414 --> 00:08:14,566
I can enjoy working here.

118
00:08:14,566 --> 00:08:15,888
I see.

119
00:08:16,251 --> 00:08:19,048
I'd started it just before
the Showa era ended.

120
00:08:19,048 --> 00:08:21,039
-It's over 30 years, then?
-Yes.

121
00:08:21,039 --> 00:08:22,352
Congratulations!

122
00:08:22,352 --> 00:08:23,579
Thank you!

123
00:08:23,579 --> 00:08:24,787
Here, come on.

124
00:08:37,242 --> 00:08:38,242
Thank you.

125
00:08:43,068 --> 00:08:45,943
I heard you have fond memories
about chicken rice.

126
00:08:47,052 --> 00:08:51,468
When I was little, this was our main dish
for celebrations, like my birthday.

127
00:08:52,619 --> 00:08:55,161
Akai grew up in an orphanage.

128
00:08:55,677 --> 00:08:58,468
Shinichiro Akai is not his real name.

129
00:08:58,966 --> 00:09:01,841
The name was given to him
by the head of the orphanage.

130
00:09:02,147 --> 00:09:04,664
This photo was taken
after he was brought to...

131
00:09:04,664 --> 00:09:07,258
-Today's story is quite somber, isn't it?
-Yes.

132
00:09:08,748 --> 00:09:11,956
You can hear
that kind of story everywhere.

133
00:09:13,501 --> 00:09:15,959
That was hard for me
as I can't change my past.

134
00:09:17,067 --> 00:09:21,150
That's why I decided to overwrite my life,

135
00:09:22,448 --> 00:09:26,573
-and stop worrying about who I am.
-Ma'am.

136
00:09:27,276 --> 00:09:28,401
-Ma'am.
-What?

137
00:09:29,180 --> 00:09:30,899
Can I have whiskey and water?

138
00:09:31,163 --> 00:09:32,080
Sure.

139
00:09:36,103 --> 00:09:37,270
I, your mother...

140
00:09:38,624 --> 00:09:40,624
I wanted to see you so much, Shin.

141
00:09:42,378 --> 00:09:45,545
On the program, I said

142
00:09:46,522 --> 00:09:49,314
that's how I remembered
my mother called me.

143
00:09:49,939 --> 00:09:51,731
That's why you call me that, right?

144
00:09:52,020 --> 00:09:53,770
Don't be silly.

145
00:09:54,045 --> 00:09:56,721
You are my Shin.

146
00:09:57,719 --> 00:09:59,489
Can you take a DNA test?

147
00:10:01,040 --> 00:10:04,676
You're the son of your father's ex-wife,

148
00:10:04,676 --> 00:10:07,671
so I'm not your biological mother.

149
00:10:10,782 --> 00:10:13,532
Many women turned up
and claimed to be his mom?

150
00:10:13,686 --> 00:10:15,811
After watching Mr. Akai's documentary?

151
00:10:16,413 --> 00:10:19,311
He talked about it, laughing,

152
00:10:19,311 --> 00:10:22,238
but he hasn't been here for a while.

153
00:10:23,314 --> 00:10:25,107
I can see how depressed he must be,

154
00:10:25,405 --> 00:10:28,572
because he knows
all they want is his money.

155
00:10:29,094 --> 00:10:31,219
Master looks depressed as well.

156
00:10:31,911 --> 00:10:33,089
Why?

157
00:10:33,326 --> 00:10:35,409
What? Well...

158
00:10:36,020 --> 00:10:38,181
He was so worried about
running out of ingredients,

159
00:10:38,181 --> 00:10:41,431
thinking many viewers would rush in here
after the documentary.

160
00:10:42,258 --> 00:10:43,591
But it didn't happen.

161
00:10:44,849 --> 00:10:48,823
Master! We are here to support you!

162
00:10:49,694 --> 00:10:51,360
It turned out to be
nothing to worry about.

163
00:10:51,830 --> 00:10:53,830
It was a good thing in the end, right?

164
00:10:56,751 --> 00:10:58,792
-He expected more customers?
-Of course.

165
00:10:58,792 --> 00:11:01,125
Otherwise, he wouldn't say "in the end."

166
00:11:07,011 --> 00:11:08,178
Welcome.

167
00:11:14,763 --> 00:11:18,346
I watched the program the other day--

168
00:11:18,346 --> 00:11:19,179
Wow!

169
00:11:19,605 --> 00:11:22,546
Master, see? It attracted a customer!

170
00:11:23,505 --> 00:11:24,338
Yeah.

171
00:11:26,978 --> 00:11:29,062
Do you play video games?

172
00:11:29,931 --> 00:11:32,889
No way. I'm here for his chicken rice.

173
00:11:34,825 --> 00:11:37,200
Could I have a chicken rice, please?

174
00:11:37,444 --> 00:11:39,527
It looked so delicious on TV.

175
00:11:39,930 --> 00:11:41,180
Sure.

176
00:11:52,500 --> 00:11:54,250
Is this the game?

177
00:11:54,827 --> 00:11:57,286
Right. It'll be finally on sale.

178
00:12:00,458 --> 00:12:01,292
A long time ago,

179
00:12:02,549 --> 00:12:05,591
I used to make this dish often.

180
00:12:06,688 --> 00:12:08,563
For your children?

181
00:12:09,681 --> 00:12:10,514
Yes.

182
00:12:11,216 --> 00:12:12,049
Excuse me...

183
00:12:13,108 --> 00:12:16,521
The man who was interviewed...
Does he come here?

184
00:12:17,966 --> 00:12:19,841
He must be very busy these days.

185
00:12:20,583 --> 00:12:22,458
I haven't seen him recently.

186
00:12:23,992 --> 00:12:25,159
I see.

187
00:13:02,056 --> 00:13:04,389
I'll check the schedule now.

188
00:13:06,931 --> 00:13:09,056
We don't have time for this.

189
00:13:19,872 --> 00:13:22,831
You seem so exhausted.

190
00:13:24,003 --> 00:13:25,878
Because of my age, perhaps.

191
00:13:26,342 --> 00:13:29,134
I feel exhausted
after working through the night.

192
00:13:39,736 --> 00:13:41,528
She came here after watching the program

193
00:13:42,365 --> 00:13:44,448
because the chicken rice looked good.

194
00:13:45,033 --> 00:13:48,221
Is that so? I like it very much, too.

195
00:13:55,819 --> 00:13:56,944
I'm so sorry...

196
00:13:58,425 --> 00:13:59,300
Shin.

197
00:14:15,321 --> 00:14:17,863
Your father had...

198
00:14:18,856 --> 00:14:20,064
a wife...

199
00:14:21,054 --> 00:14:22,638
and a child.

200
00:14:24,167 --> 00:14:26,750
He said I could have the baby

201
00:14:27,639 --> 00:14:29,639
but he couldn't officially
acknowledge you.

202
00:14:31,504 --> 00:14:34,004
He left me in the end.

203
00:14:35,257 --> 00:14:38,174
I tried my best to raise you alone...

204
00:14:40,482 --> 00:14:42,602
But I had no skills to get a job,

205
00:14:42,602 --> 00:14:45,644
and it was too much to take
for a 20-year-old girl.

206
00:14:48,922 --> 00:14:50,839
My parents cut ties with me.

207
00:14:52,756 --> 00:14:55,631
I didn't have anyone to talk to.

208
00:14:57,287 --> 00:14:59,641
I thought about killing both of us.

209
00:15:00,029 --> 00:15:01,820
How selfish.

210
00:15:04,752 --> 00:15:06,430
Please don't get me wrong.

211
00:15:07,566 --> 00:15:11,400
I didn't say that,
thinking you're my mother.

212
00:15:14,324 --> 00:15:15,574
Then...

213
00:15:17,604 --> 00:15:20,312
I thought we should have good memories
before we die...

214
00:15:23,615 --> 00:15:25,490
and we went to an amusement park.

215
00:15:27,961 --> 00:15:30,045
When I was looking at your happy face...

216
00:15:31,861 --> 00:15:34,111
I felt scared to take your life with me.

217
00:15:36,621 --> 00:15:38,746
You said, "I want to get on that one."

218
00:15:43,117 --> 00:15:44,908
I left you there and ran away.

219
00:15:48,946 --> 00:15:52,801
It was on a horse of a merry-go-round.

220
00:15:55,595 --> 00:15:57,012
In the end,

221
00:15:57,829 --> 00:15:59,620
you couldn't kill yourself.

222
00:16:01,984 --> 00:16:03,368
That's disgusting.

223
00:16:06,687 --> 00:16:09,729
I don't have a mother.

224
00:16:10,843 --> 00:16:14,431
She can't call herself a mother, either,
because she abandoned me.

225
00:16:15,313 --> 00:16:16,313
You're right.

226
00:16:17,871 --> 00:16:23,529
I have no rights to be your mother
after all these years.

227
00:16:47,277 --> 00:16:50,902
Red color suits you very much,

228
00:16:52,547 --> 00:16:53,839
Shinichi.

229
00:17:10,717 --> 00:17:14,383
I could survive without having parents...

230
00:17:15,717 --> 00:17:17,701
I believed so.

231
00:17:22,639 --> 00:17:24,347
Why should I change that now?

232
00:17:35,909 --> 00:17:37,263
Here you go.

233
00:17:38,963 --> 00:17:40,005
Is this...

234
00:17:41,650 --> 00:17:45,007
"He refused to eat peas,

235
00:17:45,890 --> 00:17:49,057
but he started eating them
when I put peas like this."

236
00:17:50,280 --> 00:17:51,822
Your mother told me so.

237
00:17:55,193 --> 00:17:56,360
That woman...

238
00:17:58,133 --> 00:18:01,029
She called me Shinichi.

239
00:18:01,486 --> 00:18:02,542
Is that your real name?

240
00:18:04,194 --> 00:18:05,110
Yes.

241
00:18:08,226 --> 00:18:09,434
I've been told...

242
00:18:12,082 --> 00:18:14,082
that only a note with my real name

243
00:18:15,699 --> 00:18:18,615
was in my pocket when I was found.

244
00:18:20,924 --> 00:18:21,758
In addition...

245
00:18:24,122 --> 00:18:26,956
the fact that I was found
at the merry-go-round...

246
00:18:29,194 --> 00:18:30,819
Only a handful of people know that.

247
00:18:35,206 --> 00:18:37,622
She knew she was not
in a position to see you,

248
00:18:39,412 --> 00:18:41,287
but she came here to do so, I guess?

249
00:18:45,247 --> 00:18:46,664
For the last two weeks...

250
00:18:48,277 --> 00:18:49,860
she came in every day,

251
00:18:52,203 --> 00:18:54,495
thinking you would turn up any minute.

252
00:18:55,367 --> 00:18:59,224
She had been waiting for you,
feeling scared.

253
00:19:41,116 --> 00:19:42,450
When I was rescued,

254
00:19:43,373 --> 00:19:45,289
I was wearing a red jacket.

255
00:19:46,413 --> 00:19:48,034
I kept wearing...

256
00:19:49,313 --> 00:19:50,688
the red jacket...

257
00:19:52,936 --> 00:19:54,352
until it was threadbare.

258
00:19:59,651 --> 00:20:01,359
Because I wanted her to find me.

259
00:20:07,579 --> 00:20:11,454
I wanted my mother to find me...

260
00:20:12,932 --> 00:20:15,016
for a very long time.

261
00:20:28,603 --> 00:20:30,508
A while later,

262
00:20:30,805 --> 00:20:33,930
Mr. Akai's new game was released.

263
00:20:40,062 --> 00:20:41,103
See you.

264
00:20:45,729 --> 00:20:46,989
It was delicious.

265
00:20:50,489 --> 00:20:51,697
Mr. Momi,

266
00:20:52,681 --> 00:20:54,390
you look exhausted.

267
00:20:55,175 --> 00:20:57,842
So do you.
You haven't had much sleep, have you?

268
00:20:58,960 --> 00:21:04,719
They're so hooked on the game,
without having enough sleep every night.

269
00:21:07,123 --> 00:21:09,040
It takes away my time.

270
00:21:10,679 --> 00:21:13,387
Instead of getting angry
about my time being taken away,

271
00:21:13,831 --> 00:21:15,581
I'd like to thank it.

272
00:21:16,040 --> 00:21:19,248
Talk about a crazy contradiction.

273
00:21:20,582 --> 00:21:22,623
I want to tell him about this feeling.

274
00:21:25,105 --> 00:21:26,329
Do you think Mr. Akai is coming here?

275
00:21:27,308 --> 00:21:28,433
Who knows.

276
00:21:29,095 --> 00:21:33,764
It seems he's found another place
that serves better chicken rice.

277
00:21:47,283 --> 00:21:48,367
Welcome.

278
00:22:04,958 --> 00:22:06,124
Here is the menu.

279
00:22:08,757 --> 00:22:12,091
Beer and a chicken rice, please.

280
00:22:12,926 --> 00:22:14,009
Sure.

281
00:22:20,308 --> 00:22:22,725
No worries. I'll do it myself.

282
00:22:24,234 --> 00:22:26,275
I'm starving.

283
00:22:28,110 --> 00:22:29,068
Okay.

284
00:22:29,918 --> 00:22:31,501
Wait a minute.

285
00:23:04,599 --> 00:23:08,599
RAMEN

286
00:23:11,996 --> 00:23:14,579
A parent and a child, who lived apart
for several decades,

287
00:23:15,338 --> 00:23:18,713
they met again at Midnight Diner.
They had some issues at first,

288
00:23:19,196 --> 00:23:20,737
but I heard they made amends.

289
00:23:23,815 --> 00:23:26,190
That kind of thing happens at his place.

290
00:23:29,114 --> 00:23:32,364
People can reconcile.

291
00:23:35,114 --> 00:23:37,114
Isn't that nice once in a while?

292
00:23:39,302 --> 00:23:40,385
Right.

